orical account of the debates, events, and personalities behind the beginnings of the nation’s political parties. This includes the importance of national party nominating conventions in the nineteenth century, the growing importance of primary elections in nominations beginning in the early twentieth century, and the changes of campaigning for presidential candidates as they started to travel across the United States for the first time in the early twentieth century. The book tells the story of the beginnings of nationally televised presidential debates and any number of other changes in the era of broadcasting and now digital platforms for presidential elections in the twenty-first century. It finishes with a look at political dynamics since the November 2020 election and a study of negative partisanship to define how campaigning for the White House works today.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPolitical partieszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aRight and left (Political science)zUnited StatesxHistory. 4aDemokratische Partei. 4aPräsidentschaft. 4aRepublikanische Partei. 4aWahl. 4aWahlkampf. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / General.2bisacsh  aCampaigns.  aDemocrats.  aElections.  aPresidency.  aRepublicans.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z97831113321920 cEPUBz97831113401590 cprintz978311133989440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311134002940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111340029423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111340029/original  a978-3-11-133219-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1b2024  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles